\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. P. maritima} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 114 (1753). Perennial with several or many rosettes; stock laxly branched, leafy only at the apex. Leaves (2-)3-25 × 0·2-1·5 cm, linear, usually entire, usually long-attenuate at the apex, slightly fleshy and coriaceous, not rigid, more or less canaliculate, glabrous or subglabrous except for sericeous hairs at the base. Scapes numerous, usually exceeding the leaves, stout. Spikes (1-)3-7(-10) × 0·3-0·4 cm, lax. Bracts ovate-lanceolate, acute, strongly keeled, narrowly scarious at margin, about equalling the calyx. Anterior sepals with the membranous margins of unequal width; posterior sepals with keel unwinged. Capsule 2-locular; seeds 2-4, 2-2·5 mm. 2n = 12, 18, 24.{\i  Maritime habitats, and on saline or base-rich soils inland. Most of Europe, but rare in the extreme south}. All except Az Bl Bu Cr Gr Sb Tu.
