\pard\f0\fs28   Various attempts have been made to subdivide this rather variable species, but the taxa proposed have proved difficult to define morphologically. Plants from Arctic Europe have been assigned to subsp.{\b  juncoides} (Lam.) Hultén,{\i  Kungl. Svenska Vet. Akad. Handl.} ser. 4, {\b 8}: 15 (1958), which is considered to differ from the widespread subsp.{\b  maritima} in having wide bracts, more ovoid to globose capsule, the scapes not exceeding the leaves and more numerous seeds per capsule, but these criteria have not proved very satisfactory.
